AND THATS WHY, I don’t use my legal last name on my profiles so I can hide them from employers. I’ll post whatever I want, it’s my profile. It’s not on your company page, or tagged into your company page and idk why companies even want their names attached to people’s personal profiles? People are allowed personal time and personal interests. I can’t stand people who mix work and real life. Find balance and let people live. It’s kind of pathetic not to hire someone because you crept their personal profiles and didn’t like a few selfies due to their context. Just ask them not to associate their personal lives with your business. It’s simple.

Yuck I hate 2020.
